Hey, we're adding a new feature: chat-embedded forms. Sometimes the AI will 
respond with a structured form for the user to fill (e.g., "Apply for Leave" 
or "Log Hours") instead of plain text. You need to build a generic 
FormRenderer that handles any form spec the backend sends.

This is additive — natural-language chat keeps working exactly as before.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
WHAT CHANGES IN THE CHAT STREAM
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

Currently the chat stream sends only text chunks:

    data: {"type": "chunk", "text": "..."}

Now a NEW chunk type will appear: "form".

    data: {"type": "form", "form_spec": { ... }}

When you receive this, render an HTML form INSIDE the chat (as a chat bubble), 
based on the form_spec JSON. Don't render it as text.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
THE form_spec SHAPE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

Example form_spec the backend will send:

{
  "version": 1,
  "form_id": "hrms_apply_leave",
  "title": "Apply for Leave",
  "description": "Submit a new leave request",
  "submit_label": "Submit Request",
  "cancel_label": "Cancel",
  "fields": [
    {
      "name": "leave_type_id",
      "label": "Leave Type",
      "type": "select",
      "required": true,
      "options": [
        {"value": 1, "label": "Casual Leave (10 left)"},
        {"value": 2, "label": "Sick Leave (8 left)"},
        {"value": 3, "label": "Earned Leave (15 left)"}
      ],
      "default": 1
    },
    {
      "name": "from_date",
      "label": "From Date",
      "type": "date",
      "required": true,
      "default": "2026-06-15"
    },
    {
      "name": "to_date",
      "label": "To Date",
      "type": "date",
      "required": true
    },
    {
      "name": "reason",
      "label": "Reason",
      "type": "textarea",
      "required": true,
      "max_length": 500,
      "placeholder": "Brief explanation"
    }
  ]
}

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
FIELD TYPES TO SUPPORT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

Build the FormRenderer to handle ALL these types. Phase 1 forms use only 
text, textarea, number, date, select — but plan for the rest.

  text:      <input type="text">
  textarea:  <textarea>
  number:    <input type="number">
  date:      <input type="date">  (browser native picker is fine)
  select:    <select> with options[]
  checkbox:  <input type="checkbox">

Common attributes ALL fields may have:
  - name (string, required): the key in submission data
  - label (string, required): visible label above the input
  - type (string, required): one of above
  - required (bool): show asterisk; block submit if empty
  - default (any): pre-fill value (especially common for date/select)
  - placeholder (string): input placeholder text
  - help_text (string): small grey text below input
  - min_length / max_length: for text/textarea
  - min / max: for number/date
  - options (array of {value, label}): for select only

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
RENDERING REQUIREMENTS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

1. Render the form as a chat bubble (NOT a modal, NOT a side panel). It 
   appears inline in the chat scroll, like a styled message from the AI.

2. The form has:
   - Title at the top (form_spec.title)
   - Optional description text (form_spec.description) if provided
   - All fields rendered in order
   - Submit button (label = form_spec.submit_label or "Submit")
   - Cancel button (label = form_spec.cancel_label or "Cancel")

3. Form styling should match your existing chat UI — same fonts, colors, 
   rounded corners. The form should feel like part of the conversation.

4. Use the `default` value to pre-fill inputs when the form first renders.

5. Required fields show a visual indicator (red asterisk after label, 
   "Required" text, or whatever fits your design language).

6. While a form is showing, the user can STILL type in the chat input 
   normally. The form is non-blocking. Both the input and form coexist.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
CLIENT-SIDE VALIDATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

Validate before sending to backend:
  - Required fields filled (not empty/null)
  - min_length / max_length for text fields
  - min / max for number/date
  - Date format YYYY-MM-DD (HTML date input enforces this)
  - For select: value must be one of options

Show inline error message below the offending field. Don't disable submit 
preemptively — let user click submit, then highlight all errors at once.

Backend will ALSO validate (defense in depth) and return an error message 
if anything slips through.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
SUBMIT BEHAVIOR
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

When user clicks Submit and all validations pass:

1. Disable the Submit button (prevent double-clicks).

2. Send a POST to /api/v1/chat/stream with this payload:

   {
     "collection_name": "<same collection the chat is in, e.g., HRMS>",
     "form_submission": {
       "form_id": "<from form_spec.form_id>",
       "data": {
         "leave_type_id": 1,
         "from_date": "2026-06-15",
         "to_date": "2026-06-16",
         "reason": "Personal work"
       }
     }
   }

   Notes:
     - Do NOT send a "message" field for form submissions.
     - Do NOT send "agent_role".
     - Do NOT send "chat_history" — the backend reconstructs context from form_id.
     - Authorization: Bearer <access_token> as usual.

3. The backend responds with an SSE stream (same /chat/stream endpoint). 
   Process chunks normally. The agent will send back a text confirmation 
   like "Leave request #5 submitted, pending approval."

4. After successful submission, REPLACE the form bubble with a small 
   "Submitted ✓" badge or summary. Don't leave the editable form around.

5. The agent's text confirmation appears as a NEW chat bubble below the 
   submitted form.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
CANCEL BEHAVIOR
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

When user clicks Cancel:

1. Remove the form from the chat (replace with a faded "Form cancelled" 
   message or just remove the bubble).

2. Send a POST to /api/v1/chat/stream with:

   {
     "collection_name": "<same collection>",
     "message": "I cancelled the form."
   }

   This is just a regular text message. The AI will acknowledge ("No problem, 
   let me know if you need anything else") and conversation continues.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
COMPLETE FLOW EXAMPLE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

User types in HRMS chat: "I want to apply for leave"

→ Frontend sends: POST /chat/stream with message + collection_name

→ Backend processes, agent decides to show form

→ SSE stream sends: data: {"type": "form", "form_spec": {form definition}}

→ Frontend receives "form" type → renders FormRenderer inline as chat bubble

→ User fills fields and clicks "Submit Request"

→ Frontend validates → sends POST /chat/stream with form_submission payload

→ Backend processes submission, agent confirms

→ SSE stream sends: data: {"type": "chunk", "text": "Leave request #7 
   submitted, pending approval."}

→ Frontend replaces form with "Submitted ✓" → shows confirmation as new bubble

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
WHAT IS NOT CHANGING
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

  - All existing chat behavior continues to work
  - Natural-language chat still routes through the same /chat/stream endpoint
  - Forms are ADDITIONAL — they don't replace typing
  - JWT, login, capabilities, timesheet endpoints — no changes
  - SSE event format for text chunks — unchanged

═══════════════════════════════════════════════
ERROR HANDLING
═══════════════════════════════════════════════

If the form_spec JSON is malformed (missing fields, unknown field type, 
etc.):
  → Log to console, render a fallback text message in chat:
    "The AI tried to send a form but it was malformed. Please try again."

If form submission fails (HTTP 4xx/5xx or chunk contains error text):
  → Keep the form visible with the entered values (don't lose user data)
  → Re-enable Submit button
  → Display the error message above the form buttons

